## Indicators of Compromise (IOCs)

| Type | Value | Verdict |
|------|-------|---------|
| IP | 4.2.2.1 | CLEAN — Level 3 public DNS server |
| IP | 172.16.16.154 | CLEAN — Internal client host |
| IP | 68.71.212.158 | CLEAN — ESPN server |
| IP | 199.181.133.61 | CLEAN — ESPN/Disney server |
| IP | 72.21.91.8 | CLEAN — Edgecast CDN |
| IP | 72.246.56.35 | CLEAN — Akamai CDN |
| IP | 72.246.56.83 | CLEAN — Akamai CDN |
| IP | 69.31.75.194 | CLEAN — Akamai CDN |
| IP | 69.31.75.203 | CLEAN — Akamai CDN |
| Domain | www.espn.com | CLEAN — Legitimate sports website |
| Domain | cdn.optimizely.com | CLEAN — Known analytics platform |

---

## Conclusions

1. No malicious activity detected. All domains resolved are
   legitimate and associated with ESPN and its CDN infrastructure.

2. Normal web browsing pattern confirmed. The timing and volume
   of DNS queries is consistent with a single page load of espn.com.

3. Client behavior is expected. Internal host 172.16.16.154 used
   a public DNS server (4.2.2.1) which, while functional, represents
   a configuration worth noting — organizations typically enforce
   internal DNS servers to maintain visibility and control.

4. CDN usage is legitimate. Multiple Akamai and Edgecast IPs
   resolving for espncdn.com domains is standard CDN load balancing
   behavior, not suspicious activity.

---

## Recommendations

| # | Recommendation | Priority |
|---|----------------|----------|
| 1 | Enforce internal DNS server usage via DHCP policy to prevent clients using public DNS 4.2.2.1 — improves visibility and control | Medium |
| 2 | Implement DNS logging at the network level to maintain full query history for future investigations | High |
| 3 | Monitor for DNS queries to unusual TLDs or high-entropy domain names which may indicate DNS tunneling or C2 activity | High |
| 4 | Whitelist known CDN IP ranges from Akamai, Cloudflare, Edgecast in threat intelligence platform to reduce false positives | Low |

